    public class | source

    Suite

    A set of Benchmarks for executing those sequential or parallel.

    Example:

    import {Suite} from 'promise-bench';


new Suite({
    beforeEach() {
        this.text = 'hello world';
    },
    async: true,
})
.add(function() {
    /o/.test(this.text);
})
.add({
    name: 'String#indexOf'
    before() {
        console.log('starting String#indexOf...');
    },
    fun() {
        this.text.indexOf('o') > -1;
    },
})
.add({
    name: 'String#match'
    fun() {
        !!this.text.match(/o/);
    },
    after(result) {
        console.log('String#match is done! ' + result);
    },
})
.run()

    public async afterSuite(results: Result[]): Promise source

    Teardown after execute all benchmarks.

    At the time executing this method, this is the unique object for the suite. So you can use this for storing testing data like a database. Data of this that set in this method will discard after call this method.

    In default, do nothing.

    Params:

    NameTypeAttributeDescription
    results Result[]

    a list of benchmark result.

    Return:

    Promise (nullable: true)

    public async beforeSuite(): Promise source

    Setup before execute all benchmarks.

    At the time executing this method, this is the unique object for the suite. So you can use this for storing testing data like a database. Data of this that set in this method will discard after call Suite#afterSuite

    In default, do nothing.

    Return:

    Promise (nullable: true)

    public async run(context: Object): Promise<Result[]> source

    Execute benchmarks in this suite.

    All benchmarks will execute parallel if enabled Suite#async option. Else do execute sequentially by added order.

    Params:

    NameTypeAttributeDescription
    context Object
    • optional

    the this for each benchmarking functions.

    Return:

    Promise<Result[]>
